作者 | 中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴编辑 | 曲俊燕3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院15层发热病区，这里的患者已经悉数转院或出院，留下空荡荡的病房。
At the afternoon of March 17, the 15th floor of Wuhan Red Cross Hospital was turned over or discharged, leaving an empty ward.
该医院是1月22日武汉市第一批收治发热患者的7家定点医院之一。
The hospital was one of the first seven hospitals in Wuhan on January 22 to treat febrile patients.
目前，该医院已被列为普通患者就医医院，从3月18日8时起，预计将暂时关停7天，以进行全面消杀。
The hospital is now classified as a general patient hospital and is expected to be temporarily closed for seven days from 8 a.m. on 18 March for full elimination.
医院在公告中同时提醒广大病友在此期间就近选择其他医疗机构就诊。
Hospital in the announcement also reminded the majority of patients in the period of the nearest choice of other medical institutions.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院，医护人员护送一名危重症患者转院。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing net reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 17 afternoon, Wuhan City Red Cross Hospital, medical personnel escorted a critically ill patient to hospital.
他们中的部分人将随救护车前往定点收治新冠肺炎重症患者的同济医院光谷院区，随时监控患者情况。
Some of them will follow the ambulance to the Tongji Hospital in Tongji Hospital, where patients with severe pneumonia are treated, to monitor the situation at any time.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院，一名危重症患者转院后，黄晓波和同事梳理病人转院流程上的问题。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongqing Zhonghe, reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 17 afternoon, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, a critically ill patient was transferred to hospital, Huang Xiaobo and colleagues combed the patients transfer process problems.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科一病区，一名上了ECMO（人工膜肺）的患者准备转院，医护人员紧急为其吸痰、调整呼吸和输液管道，本在休息的部分医护人员也从驻地前来帮忙。
In the afternoon of March 17, a patient admitted to ECMO (Artificial Membrane Lung) was transferred to hospital for emergency treatment of phlegm, breathing and infusion lines. Some of Ben's rest medical staff also came from the station to help.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院，几名医护人员推着空病床演练危重症病人转院流程。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongqing reported that on the afternoon of March 17, 2007, at Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, several medical workers rehearsed the transfer process of critically ill patients with empty beds.
危重症病人身上插有约10根管道，需要呼吸机等设备维持生命，医护人员需要确保患者、设备和随行医护人员能同时通过狭窄的楼道、进入电梯和救护车。
Some 10 pipes are inserted into critically ill patients and life-sustaining devices such as ventilators are required to ensure that patients, equipment and accompanying medical staff can pass through the narrow aisles, access elevators and ambulances simultaneously.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科一病区，医护人员在研究如何使用氧气瓶给呼吸机供氧。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, reported that on the afternoon of March 17, 2007, in the respiratory department of Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, medical staff were studying how to supply oxygen to the ventilator with oxygen cylinders.
当日，该病区的仅剩的6名危重症患者有5名转院，医护人员需要确保患者在转院途中的安全。
On that day, five of the remaining six critically ill patients in the area were referred to hospital, and health-care staff were required to ensure the safety of patients on their way to hospital.
3月19日上午，该院最后一名新冠肺炎患者转院。
March 19 morning, the hospital's last new crown pneumonia patients transferred to the hospital.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日晚，武汉市红十字会医院，呼吸内科二病区，一名医生在巡床后休息。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 17 night, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, Respiratory Medicine Division 2, a doctor after a patrol bed rest.
由于防护服不透气，他坐下后，衣服被空气撑满，他笑称自己是“大白”（电影《超能陆战队》角色）。
As the suit was airtight, he sat down, his clothes stuffed with air, and he chuckled that he was "white".
3月17日晚，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科一病区，四川省援汉医疗队临时搭建的简易负压病房。
March 17 night, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital Respiratory Medicine Division I, Sichuan Province medical team set up temporary simple negative pressure ward.
新冠肺炎是一种烈性传染病，为了降低医护人员被感染风险，对患者实施插管治疗时，他们需佩戴正压头套，并在负压病房中操作。
Coronary pneumonia is a powerful infectious disease. In order to reduce the risk of infection for medical staff, patients should wear a positive head covering and operate in a negative pressure ward.
武汉市红十字会医院是一所二级医院，条件有限，没有负压病房。
Wuhan Red Cross Hospital is a level II hospital with limited conditions and no negative pressure ward.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月16日上午，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科一病区，四川省人民医院重症医学科主任黄晓波查看患者情况。
Wang Jiaxing / She March 16 morning, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital Respiratory Medicine Division I, Sichuan Province People's Hospital, severe medicine director Huang Xiaobo to check the patient situation.
这个病区已经被改造为临时ICU，收治的都是新冠肺炎危重症患者。
The area has been transformed into a makeshift ICU for patients in critical condition with Newcomial Pneumonia.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月16日上午，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科二病区，医护人员在交流患者病情。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongying. net, reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 16 morning, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital Respiratory Medicine Division 2, medical staff are exchanging patients' illness.
3月14日，这座15层楼的医院开始将患者逐步转出，恢复普通门诊。
On 14 March, the 15-storey hospital began a gradual transfer of patients from the general clinic.
截至3月16日，医院只剩下4个病区还有住院病人。
As at 16 March, only four hospital wards remained.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月16日上午，武汉市红十字会医院CT检查室，一名医生正等待患者前来检查。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing net reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 16 morning, Wuhan City Red Cross Hospital CT examination room, a doctor is waiting for patients to come for examination.
该医生表示，2月中旬起，CT室的工作强度明显减小，多数时候只需负责约300名住院患者的身体检查。
Since mid-February, CT rooms have been noticeably less intensive, the doctor said, with only about 300 in-patient visits required most of the time.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院，呼吸内科一病区，医护人员互相在衣服上画熊猫、太阳。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, reporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 17 afternoon, Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, Department of Respiratory Medicine, a sick area, medical staff painted pandas and sun on each other's clothes.
自1月27日进驻武汉市红十字会医院，四川省援汉医疗队的工作人员一直未能轮休，并高强度工作。
Since the arrival of the Wuhan Red Cross hospital on January 27, the staff of the Sichuan-Han medical team have been unable to rotate and work intensively.
高峰时，ICU的18张病床一直满床，医护人员上班时难有坐下休息的时间。
At peak hours, the ICU's 18 beds are filled with beds, making it difficult for health-care workers to sit down to work.
这个晚上，该病区只剩1人住院，并将在次日转院。
Only one person remains in the ward this evening and will be transferred the following day.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月17日下午，武汉市红十字会医院，一名护士在护士站准备注射针剂。
Zhongqing News, Zhongqing News, Zhongyingnetreporter Wang Jiaxing / She March 17 afternoon, Wuhan City Red Cross Hospital, a nurse at the nurses station to prepare injection.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄3月16日上午，武汉市红十字会医院呼吸内科一病区，一名护士将手套吹成气球，撑着氧气管，避免对患者造成压迫。
A nurse blows gloves into a balloon, holding an oxygen tube to avoid pressurization of the patient, in the morning of March 16, 2007, at Wuhan Red Cross Hospital, Department of Respiratory Medicine.
该护士告诉记者，她每吹一个气球，都会在上面写下“早日康复”等字样，表达对患者的美好愿望。
The nurse told reporters that every time she played a balloon, she would write "Early Recovery" on it to express her good wishes for the patient.
中青报·中青网记者 王嘉兴/摄中国青年报·中国青年网出品微信编辑 | 陈轶男觉得好看请点这里。
